title: ‘Drifting towards antisemitism’: Labor MPs participate in anti-Herzog demonstrations
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce condemns Labor MPs for participating in a demonstration promoting antisemitism.  “I heard that three state Labor party MPs are participating in the demonstrations,” Mr Joyce told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “Once more, we see them drifting towards antisemitism.  “After the rhetoric is over, the drift back towards antisemitism has begun.  “It falls into the category of an attack on Israel.”

title: Albanese ‘looking to raise taxes’ after spending an additional $144 billion
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson slams the Albanese government for looking to raise taxes.  “The Albanese Government is looking at raising the capital gains tax on investment properties in the May budget,” Ms Markson said.  “We're likely to see the Albanese Government take advantage of the political vacuum, of the weak opposition, to scrap tax benefits they've long hated.  “Richardson explains that since Albanese won office in 2022, there's an extra $144 billion of spending.  “He's looking to raise taxes as a result.”

title: Lefties Losing It: Netflix CEO in denial about Leftist bias
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has analysed Netflix CEO Ted Sarandos being grilled by Senator Ted Cruz.

title: The Albanese government’s getting ‘a free pass’ while the Coalition ‘crumbles'
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson criticises the Coalition for not holding the Albanese government accountable.   “The Coalition is a joke right now,” Ms Markson said.   “National senators are putting personal ego ahead of the collective good.  “The coalition is crumbling, and Albanese is getting a free pass.”

title: Lefties Losing It: Former prince's antics revealed in latest Epstein files
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has taken a look at the horrific pictures of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor featured in the Epstein files.

title: Lefties Losing It: ‘Just like Iran’ schools indoctrinate kids to hate
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has claimed the footage of schoolchildren chanting against Trump is indoctrination "just like Iran".

title: Keir Starmer on ‘shaky ground’ after astonishing Epstein confession
description: News Corp Correspondent Sophie Elsworth warns the UK Prime Minister is in trouble after Epstein revelations.   “In the last few days, conservative leader Kemi Badenoch asked Keir Starmer in the House of Commons if he knew that Jeffrey Epstein and Lord Mandelson maintained a relationship after he left jail,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “The Prime Minister astonishingly admitted that he did, and he went ahead and appointed him as the UK ambassador to the US.  “There is no doubt that his reign as prime minister is very much on shaky ground over this.”

title: ‘Beyond heartbreaking’: Bill Gates' ex-wife says Epstein files bring back ‘painful memories’
description: Bill Gates' ex-wife, Melinda French Gates, speaks out after her ex-husband was mentioned in the Epstein files.   “It’s beyond heartbreaking,” Ms Gates said.   “It brings back memories of some very, very painful times in my marriage.  “I can’t even begin to know all of it.  “They need to answer for those things.”

title: ‘A little creepy’: Bunnings approved to use facial recognition on customers
description: Sky News Contributor Joe Hildebrand justifies Bunnings' use of facial recognition surveillance.  “It’s a little bit creepy. It’s probably also just a little bit inevitable,” Mr Hildebrand told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “This is how cops catch crooks, and I think that’s a good thing.”

title: Barnaby Joyce could be One Nation’s first prime minister
description: Sky News Contributor Joe Hildebrand comments on his fantasy diary of Barnaby Joyce’s path to becoming One Nation’s first PM.  “Could Barnaby Joyce be One Nation's first PM?” Mr Hildebrand told Sky News host Paul Murray.   “How would that work with Pauline as the leader of the party, but Barnaby as the first prime minister.

title: Nationals don’t want three senators punished for a whole party's choice
description: Nationals Senator Ross Cadell discusses the state of the Coalition.   “All of us were prepared to cross,” Mr Cadell told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “What our party room doesn’t want to see, they don’t want to see the three senators that actually voted wear the price for the whole party when everyone was prepared to.  “You can’t single out the three guys for a decision of the whole room.”

title: Former prince Andrew claims he never met Virginia Giuffre despite photographic evidence
description: Sky News host Freya Leach mocks former prince Andrew for claiming he never met Virginia Giuffre despite photographic evidence.  “An email seemingly from Ghislaine Maxwell appears to confirm that a photograph of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor with his arm around Virginia Giuffre, who accused him of sexual abuse, is real,” Ms Leach said.  “The former prince, who has always denied any wrongdoing, has previously questioned whether the picture had been doctored and claimed he had never met Giuffre.  “He might not have any memory of it being taken, but that seems to directly contradict what has been put out in this new email.  “It’s not going well for him.”

title: ‘Move out of your house, please’: Billie Eilish grilled over Grammys stolen land comment
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond blasts Billie Eilish’s 2026 Grammys acceptance speech about stolen land.    “Billie Eilish … you would’ve seen her the other day at the Grammys making crazy comments about stolen land,” Mr Bond said.  “For goodness sake, move out of your house, please.”

title: Bunnings adopts facial recognition technology to combat crime
description: Sky News host James Macpherson details how Bunnings Warehouse has been given permission to use facial recognition technology on its clientele to combat crime.   “Next time you get your sausage from Bunnings, be aware, you’re probably being filmed,” Mr Macpherson said.  “The hardware giant has won permission to use facial recognition technology to identify problem customers.”

title: Starmer couldn’t ‘stop his hands from shaking’ when asked about Epstein
description: Sky News host Freya Leach criticises UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer for misjudgement with Mandelson.  “Peter Mandelson helped make one Labour prime minister in Tony Blair. He is about to destroy another,” Ms Leach said.  “He had to actually hold his hands down to stop them from shaking.  “They knew he was at Epstein's apartment when Epstein was in jail.”
